prompt:
In Signature.calr, add a `greeting` parameter of type `str` to the `Greet` function (f001). The function should concatenate the greeting with the name.

Before:
§F{f001:Greet:pub}
  §I{str:name}
  §O{str}
  §R name
§/F{f001}

After:
§F{f001:Greet:pub}
  §I{str:greeting}
  §I{str:name}
  §O{str}
  §R (concat greeting name)
§/F{f001}

Note: Use `(concat a b)` for string concatenation in Calor.

IMPORTANT: The function ID f001 must NOT change.
